For those who will choose the "Stay Home, Save Lives” mantra during this Christmas season, they will surely be doing the Lord’s work.
Many perks
There are many perks that they will reap from not celebrating Christmas the "normal way".
First, weight loss will not appear in their New Year resolutions because they won't have any weight to lose from unhealthy eating. Their livers and kidneys will go on holiday, knowing that there will be no excessive alcohol or sodas to keep them busy. Their bank accounts will smile, too, safe in the knowledge that there will be no unnecessary spending.
May this Christmas in a pandemic serve as a wake-up call to remember the pre-ordained purpose of the holiday, which was to celebrate the birth of Christ. And may we remember that a celebration can be achieved minus the thrills, frills and reckless spending. Amen.
